column5: Article about how we anglers are contributing:  http://mudinspired.com/blog/the-role-of-recreational-fishing-in-environmental-conservation/
Interesting. Has anyone ever explained how these invasive species are making it into these lakes?
Nice to see a young Musky come out of Dalrymple recently though....
Some idiot decides to throw it in there. I caught a weather loach in a lake in New Market. Try figuring that one out.

Interesting. Has anyone ever explained how these invasive species are making it into these lakes?  There are no doubt many different ways. Do a Google search for 'fish egg dispersal' and you'll find all sorts of info.
